      <div data-bk-layout class="pad-b rte">
        <p>BaseGrid is a standalone responsive faux grid-system built on CSS <code>inline-block</code> and the <code>data</code> attribute.</p>
        <p>Once white space has been removed, <code>inline-block</code> allows for more flexibility and more robustness than floating grid items. <code>inline-block</code> items can be vertically aligned and flow more consistently.</p>
        <p>The <code>data</code> attribute allows us to almost fully separate the layout styles from other CSS and classes.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 data-bk-layout="pad:rbl" class="font-xl">The Grid</h2>

      <div data-bk-layout class="rte">
        <p>By default BaseKit is based on the common 12 column layout, this provides great flexibility and ease of use. However you can create layouts from as many or as few columns as you wish.</p>

        <p>Unlike Bootstrap and some other systems, there are no "tiers". If you want a four column grid at small screen size simply fake it by using three columns for each small screen column.</p>
      </div>

